[SN]TITLE[SN]
Mark Beevers: Bolton Wanderers sign defender following Millwall departure

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
League One side Bolton Wanderers have signed defender Mark Beevers on a free transfer on a two-year deal.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 26-year-old left Millwall this summer after four seasons in London, where he helped the Lions reach the play-off final last term.
Beevers, who started his career at Sheffield Wednesday, also had a stint on loan at MK Dons.
He is new manager Phil Parkinson's second signing, following midfielder Chris Taylor's arrival from Blackburn.
